# Novoselskoye, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Novoselskoye (; , Kerla-Yurt) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Novoselsky Selsoviet, Khasavyurtovsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia.  There are 24 streets.
Geography
Novoselskoye is located 32&nbsp;km north of Khasavyurt (the district's administrative centre) by road. Moksob is the nearest rural locality.
